      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET IRISH LOCH (6) raced parked as a hot favourite before delivering a 4.3m win when resuming at Ballarat. Fitter and has plenty of upside so can go through her grades. There was plenty of merit in last week's resuming effort of RAKAROMPA NZ (5) when she drifted back as favourite but worked home strongly to go under by a head at Bendigo. Has won second-up before so expect she'll be improved and she is proven at this distance. Big chance. OUR BELLA LUCIA (2) must be a player again after winning from this barrier here last start. LETS GO LORNA (7) hasn't performed to market expectations in two starts off a spell but she has been tackling stronger company. Draws wide but is building in fitness so could show her best in this line-up.",
